      rating: '5', author: 'Michelle & Dave S.', date: '2025-02-28',
    },
    {
      body: "Our 1970s Bothell rambler kitchen was in rough shape. They replaced everything — layout, cabinets, counters, flooring, lighting, even moved the gas line for our new range. Project manager kept a shared folder with daily photos which was awesome since we were traveling during part of the remodel. Came out beautiful.",
      rating: '5', author: 'Kevin O.', date: '2025-01-02',
    },
    {
      body: "Second kitchen remodel with this team — first was our Kirkland home in 2022. Just finished our investment property in Renton. Both times they came in on budget and the quality is clearly above what other contractors deliver at this price point. Shaker cabinets, quartz counters, LVP flooring — clean and modern.",
      rating: '5', author: 'Linda & Robert F.', date: '2024-12-10',
    },
    {
      body: "Our Queen Anne Craftsman kitchen needed serious work — outdated from the 80s. They preserved the character of the house while modernizing everything. Period-appropriate cabinet style but with modern hardware and soft-close. Honed marble counters and a farmhouse sink. Neighbors keep stopping by to see it.",
      rating: '5', author: 'Sarah T.', date: '2024-10-15',
    },
  ],
  'bathroom-remodeling': [
